<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659a.119/4</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-07T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6476. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 75. British Embassy recommending to Foreign Office that immediate
                                steps be taken to eliminate letters of assurance on shipments to
                                Iceland and Faroe Islands with understanding that export licenses
                                will be issued only after reference to Inter-Allied Committee,
                                London, for recommendation. Is London Committee now prepared to act
                                in this matter?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>